HOUSE BILL 1165
P2 6lr1705
CF SB 673
By: Delegate Williams
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Government, Labor, and Elections
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 7, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Procurement – Apprenticeship Program Accountability and Completion
3 FOR the purpose of requiring certain apprenticeship programs utilized in certain State
4 procurements to have at least a certain completion rate, as determined by the
5 Maryland Department of Labor; and generally relating to the use of apprentices in
6 State procurement.
7 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
8 Article – State Finance and Procurement
9 Section 14–801, 14–802, 17–201, 17–205, 17–601(b), and 17–6A–01(f) 17–601, and
10 17–6A–01
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
14 Article – State Finance and Procurement
15 Section 17–601(a), (e), (f), (g), and (h), 17–602, 17–603(a), 17–604(a), 17–6A–01(a),
16 (d), and (e), and 17–6A–02(a)
17 Annotated Code of Maryland
18 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
21 Article – State Finance and Procurement
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1165*

2 HOUSE BILL 1165
1 14–801.
2 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
3 (B) “APPRENTICESHIP COHORT” MEANS A GROUP OF APPRENTICES
4 REGISTERED WITH A SPECIFIC APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM DURING A 1–YEAR
5 PERIOD, EXCLUDING ANY APPRENTICES TERMINATED DURING THEIR
6 PROBATIONARY PERIOD.
7 (C) “COMPLETION RATE” MEANS:
8 (1) FOR GROUP NONJOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAMS, THE
9 PERCENTAGE OF AN APPRENTICESHIP COHORT PER EMPLOYER THAT RECEIVES A
10 CERTIFICATE OF APPRENTICESHIP COMPLETION WITHIN 1 YEAR AFTER THE
11 PROJECTED COMPLETION DATE; OR
12 (2) FOR GROUP JOINT, INDIVIDUAL NONJOINT, INDIVIDUAL JOINT,
13 AND WAIVER APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAMS, THE PERCENTAGE OF AN
14 APPRENTICESHIP COHORT FOR THE PROGRAM THAT RECEIVES A CERTIFICATE OF
15 APPRENTICESHIP COMPLETION WITHIN 1 YEAR AFTER THE PROJECTED
16 COMPLETION DATE.
17 (b) (D) “Covered procurement” means a procurement contract that:
18 (1) meets the criteria established by the Chief Procurement Officer, in
19 consultation with the Secretary and, for contracts subject to Title 3.5 of this article, the
20 Secretary of Information Technology, under § 14–802 of this subtitle; and
21 (2) is not a public work contract subject to § 17–202 of this article.
22 (c) (E) “Department” means the Maryland Department of Labor.
23 (d) (F) “Eligible internship program” means an internship program that
24 requires a contractor or other entity to provide paid internships that meet standards
25 established by the Secretary.
26 (e) “Registered apprenticeship program” means an apprenticeship program that:
27 (1) is registered with and approved by the Division of Workforce
28 Development and Adult Learning; AND
29 (2) HAS A COMPLETION RATE OF AT LEAST 25%, AS DETERMINED BY
30 THE DEPARTMENT.

HOUSE BILL 1165 3
1 (G) “GROUP JOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN
2 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM THAT HAS A COMMITTEE, COMPOSED OF AN EQUAL
3 NUMBER OF REPRESENTATIVES OF EMPLOYERS AND EMPLOYEES, THAT HAS BEEN
4 JOINTLY ESTABLISHED BY AN EMPLOYER OR GROUP OF EMPLOYERS AND A
5 COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGENT OR AGENTS.
6 (H) “GROUP NONJOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN
7 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM SPONSORED BY TWO OR MORE EMPLOYERS WITHOUT
8 THE PARTICIPATION OF A COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGENT.
9 (I) “INDIVIDUAL JOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN
10 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM SPONSORED BY ONE EMPLOYER WITH THE
11 PARTICIPATION OF A COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGENT.
12 (J) “INDIVIDUAL NONJOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN
13 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM SPONSORED BY ONE EMPLOYER WITHOUT THE
14 PARTICIPATION OF A COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGENT.
15 (K) “REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN
16 APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM THAT:
17 (1) IS REGISTERED WITH AND APPROVED BY THE DIVISION OF
18 WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT AND ADULT LEARNING; AND
19 (2) IF THE PROGRAM HAS GRADUATED AT LEAST ONE
20 APPRENTICESHIP COHORT, HAS A COMPLETION RATE OF AT LEAST 25%, AS
21 VERIFIED BY THE DEPARTMENT.
22 (f) (L) “Secretary” means the Secretary of Labor.
23 (M) “WAIVER APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” MEANS AN APPRENTICESHIP
24 PROGRAM SPONSORED BY AN INDIVIDUAL OR GROUP OF EMPLOYERS WHERE THE
25 APPLICABLE COLLECTIVE BARGAINING AGENT WAIVED PARTICIPATION.
26 14–802.
27 (a) This subtitle applies to a covered procurement made by a unit.
28 (b) A contractor awarded a covered procurement with an estimated total dollar
29 value of $1,000,000 or more shall utilize A REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM OR
30 an eligible internship program.
31 (c) [A contractor awarded a covered procurement shall utilize a registered
32 apprenticeship program.

4 HOUSE BILL 1165
1 (d)] The Chief Procurement Officer, in consultation with the Secretary and, for
2 contracts subject to Title 3.5 of this article, the Secretary of Information Technology:
3 (1) shall adopt regulations establishing the definition of “covered
4 procurement”; and
5 (2) may adopt:
6 (i) regulations to improve the recruitment or skills of employees of
7 vendors; or
8 (ii) other regulations necessary to carry out this subtitle, including
9 waiver processes.
10 17–201.
11 (a) In this subtitle, unless the context indicates otherwise, the following words
12 have the meanings indicated.
13 (b) “Apprentice” means an individual who:
14 (1) is at least 16 years old;
15 (2) has signed with an employer or employer’s agent, an association of
16 employers, an organization of employees, or a joint committee from both, an agreement
17 including a statement of:
18 (i) the trade, craft, or occupation that the individual is learning; and
19 (ii) the beginning and ending dates of the apprenticeship; and
20 (3) is registered in a program of the Council or the Office of Apprenticeship
21 of the United States Department of Labor.
22 (c) “APPRENTICESHIP COHORT” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 14–801 OF
23 THIS ARTICLE.
24 (D) “Commissioner” means:
25 (1) the Commissioner of Labor and Industry;
26 (2) the Deputy Commissioner of Labor and Industry; or
27 (3) an authorized representative of the Commissioner.

HOUSE BILL 1165 5
1 (E) “COMPLETION RATE” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 14–801 OF THIS
2 ARTICLE.
3 [(d)] (F) “Construction” includes all:
4 (1) building;
5 (2) reconstructing;
6 (3) improving;
7 (4) enlarging;
8 (5) painting and decorating;
9 (6) altering;
10 (7) maintaining;
11 (8) repairing; and
12 (9) services provided under a mechanical systems service contract.
13 [(e)] (G) “Council” means the Apprenticeship and Training Council.
14 [(f)] (H) (1) “Employee” means an apprentice or worker employed by a
15 contractor or subcontractor under a public work contract.
16 (2) “Employee” does not include an individual employed by a public body.
17 (I) “GROUP JOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” HAS THE MEANING
18 STATED IN § 14–801 OF THIS ARTICLE.
19 (J) “GROUP NONJOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” HAS THE MEANING
20 STATED IN § 14–801 OF THIS ARTICLE.
21 (K) “INDIVIDUAL JOINT APPRENTICESHIP PROGRAM” HAS THE MEANING
