14 17–602.
15 (a) There is a State Apprenticeship Training Fund in the Department.
16 (b) The Fund consists of:
17 (1) payments made by contractors or subcontractors in accordance with
18 this subtitle and Subtitle 6A of this title;
19 (2) penalties collected as a result of violations of this subtitle and Subtitle
20 6A of this title; and
21 (3) penalties collected as a result of violations of Title 14, Subtitle 8 of this
22 article.
23 (c) The Fund is a special, nonlapsing fund that is not subject to § 7–302 of this
24 article.
25 (d) The State Treasurer shall hold the Fund separately, and the Comptroller shall
26 account for the Fund.
27 (e) The Secretary shall use money in the fund to:
28 (1) promote preapprenticeship programs and other workforce development
29 programs in the State’s public secondary schools and community colleges that assist
30 students in preparing for and entering apprenticeship training programs; and

HOUSE BILL 1165 11
1 (2) pay any costs associated with carrying out the provisions of this subtitle
2 and Subtitle 6A of this title or Title 14, Subtitle 8 of this article.
3 17–603.
4 (a) A contractor that is awarded a procurement contract for a covered project shall
5 provide to a unit, as a condition of receiving the contract, written verification that:
6 (1) the contractor participates in an apprenticeship training program for
7 each covered craft in which it will employ persons for the covered project;
8 (2) the contractor will make payments to the Fund; or
9 (3) the contractor will make payments in amounts determined under §
10 17–605 of this subtitle to a registered apprenticeship program or to an organization that
11 has registered apprenticeship programs for the purpose of supporting these programs.
12 17–604.
13 (a) A subcontractor that performs work at a value exceeding the small
14 procurement amount specified in § 13–109 of this article for a covered project shall provide
15 to a unit written verification that:
16 (1) the subcontractor participates in an apprenticeship training program
17 for each covered craft in which it will employ persons for the covered project;
18 (2) the subcontractor will make payments to the Fund; or
19 (3) the subcontractor will make payments in amounts determined under §
20 17–605 of this subtitle to a registered apprenticeship program or to an organization that
21 has registered apprenticeship programs for the purpose of supporting these programs.
